description:
Service Usage

This service allows the user to modify specific information on a visa application.
readme:
Service Usage

This service allows the user to modify specific information on a visa application.
The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a Visa Processing Officer (VPO) is required to update an application because a party has had a change of circumstances and this must be reflected in the Visa Application.
The service updates details for a specific Visa Application. The service will only deliver information which has actually changed to the backend systems, and not the entire data set.

Service Behaviour

The service updates details for a specific Visa Application. The service will only deliver information (including context) which has actually changed to the backend systems, and not the entire data set.
This service provides the following behaviour:
Checks the user initiating this business function is authorised to modify the visa application
Modifies Visa Application specific information
Modifies Visa Applicant specific information
Allows for the creation of notes specific to the Visa Application or Visa Applicant.
Allows adding new Applicants to a Visa Application.
Allows changing the association to the primary Visa Applicant and or role type
Follows an all or nothing principal for updates. This means if any particular part of the update is unable to be performed, then nothing will be updated.

The following chapters describe in detail what data types the consumer can manipulate and how the service interface is structured.
Note regarding concurrency: The current version of this service allows concurrent updates of the same data records in ICSE and thus it doesnt guarantee data consistency.
1.1.1 Data Types which can be manipulated by this service
SV012 allows manipulating the following CDM data types and operations:
Updating, Inserting and Deleting of Single Attributes of Visa Application or Visa Applicant
Updating, Inserting and Deleting of Child Objects of Visa Application or Visa Applicant
Inserting of Notes (Notes Portal, Client Notes and Case Notes)
Updating of Person Visa Application Role And Or Association
Inserting/deleting of Visa Applicants

The handling of the different data types is described in the following chapters.
1.1.1.1 Child Objects of Visa Application and Visa Applicant
If the Consumer intends to update, insert or delete Child Objects (which are the CDM representation of ICSE events) it needs to provide the following data

CDM Identifier for the Child Object (in case of UPDATE and DELETE)
Operation (UPDATE, INSERT or DELETE)
Fully populated Child with all related Attributes (in case of UPDATE and INSERT)

Remark: SV012 allows updating, inserting and deleting of multiple Child Objects, Attributes and Notes at the same time in a single transaction.
1.1.1.1 Single Attributes of Visa Application or Visa Applicant
If the Consumer intends to update, insert or delete an attribute (which is the CDM representation of an ICSE PermissionRequestInfo) of the Visa Application or Visa Applicant it needs to provide the following data:
ICSE Sequence number if the attribute has an ICSE Multiplicity > 1 (in case of DELETE and UPDATE)
CDM Attribute with its new value (in case of UPDATE and INSERT)
SV012 applies the following logic to determine which operation (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) the consumer intends to have processed:

Seq Number is present Value is present, i.e., node is not nil. Operation
n/a yes UPDATE or INSERT
n/a no DELETE
Table 1: Determine the operation of Single Attributes with multiplicity = 1

Seq Number is present Value is present, i.e., node is not nil. Operation
no yes INSERT
yes no DELETE
yes yes UPDATE=DELETE +INSERT
Table 2: Determine the operation of Single Attributes with multiplicity > 1

In the case of UPDATE for multiplicity > 1, first the DELETE operation has to be performed followed by INSERT.
1.1.1.2 Inserting Notes
If the Consumer intends to insert a Note (Notes Portal, Client Notes or Case Notes) it needs to provide the following data:
For Notes Portal
Application ID
AssociationType (In ICSE terms this represents a Qualifier)
Mandatory AssociationId (This is stored in ICSE as EventAdditionalInfo)
Complete Notes Context

For Case Notes
Application ID
Complete Notes Context

For Client Notes
Application ID
Applicant ID
Role
Complete Notes Context
SV012 allows only inserting notes. Deletes und Updates of Notes are not possible.

Remark: SV012 allows inserting of notes and inserting, updating and deleting of child objects and attributes at the same time in one transaction.
1.1.1.3 Updating Role and or association to primary applicant
If the Consumer intends to update the association to the primary applicant and or Role it needs to provide the following data:
Application ID
Applicant ID
Current Role
New Role (Required for update of role)
Association details (Required for update of association)
SV012 allows only updating the role and or association of a Visa Applicant. Inserts and deletes are not possible as it assumes update of role for applicants already present in the application. Even if only update of role is intended, association details are also mandatory to be sent. For only update of association to primary applicant, new role need not be sent. For update of both association and role, all the above mentioned fields are required to be sent.
Restriction: If the consumer intends to change the Role of a Visa Applicant and to change the association, the service call does not allow changes to other data elements at the same time.
1.1.1.4 Inserting/deleting Visa Applicants
If the consumer intends to insert/delete a client it needs to provide the following data:
Application ID
Applicant ID
Role
Restriction: If the consumer intends to insert/delete clients, the service does not allow any other data manipulations at the same time.

1.1.2 Choice Groups
The XSD of SV012 contains a choice group element in order to provide a structured interface to the consumer. The choice group element allows one of the following children
ModifyVisaApplicationOrApplicantDetails
ModifyApplicant
These children are of complex type and contain all variant specific Elements.
1.1.2.1 ModifyVisaApplicationOrApplicantDetails
This choice group provides the ability to update, insert and delete one or many data items belonging to a Visa Application or Visa Applicant(s). Data consists of information from any of the following CDM Subject Areas:
Visa Application
Follow up Alerts
Person Visa Applicant
GSM Person Visa Application
Person Visa Application Claim
ASCO Code
Party Relationship
Regional Australian Address
Person Factors (Employment, Language, Police Check, Country Stay, Qualification)
Values Statement
Notes (Portal Notes, Case Notes and Client notes)
No Adverse Information
1.1.2.2 ModifyApplicant
This choice group allows adding new Applicants to a Visa Application, modifying the association of a particular Applicant to the primary Applicant, and or change the role of the Visa Applicant.
1.1.3 Response Message
A consumer of this service receives either:
An Enterprise Service Acknowledgement, or
An Enterprise Error if the Visa Application cannot be modified for whatever reason.

Service Dependencies

A Visa Application must be existent in the provider system.

Service Composition

There is no composition call.

Service Flow

In general this service processes incoming requests in 2 steps

  1. The service creates a message dependent on which element of the choice group is filled and what operation the consumer intends to process.
  2. Sending the request message to ICSE
    The following chapters describe the behaviour of the service for each element of the choice group differently.
    1.1.1 ModifyVisaApplicationOrApplicantDetails
    1.1.1.1 Service Flow for ModifyApplicantOrApplicantDetails
    The service receives the request message from the consumer. The Message can contain single Attributes (ICSE: Permission Request Infos), Child Objects of the Visa Application (ICSE: Events) and Notes (either Notes Portal or Case Notes).

Based to some rules (see Chapter 1.2.1 Data Types which can be manipulated by this service) the Flow determines the operation (Delete, Update and Insert) for each element. Then the Flow sends an accordingly populated ApplicationMaintenanceRequest message to ICSE. ICSE will then execute this request and return an acknowledgement message back to service SV012 where a response message is returned to the consumer.

The detail of this flow is as follows:

  1. Service consumer invokes service SV012 on ESB using ModifyVisaApplicationRequest.
  2. SV012 creates an ICSE request message according to the rules described in chapter 2.1 (ICSE Service Provider).
    a. For each single Attribute a PermissionRequestInfo-Element is created.
    b. For each Child Object at least one Event-Element is created.
    c. For each Note one Event-Element is created.
  3. Service SV012 invokes ICSE sending the request message.
  4. ICSE receives the request and tries to processes the updates for the specified visa application or the specified Visa Applicant(s).
  5. ICSE then sends an acknowledgement message back to service SV012.
  6. Service SV012 sends a successful response message to the consumer.
    1.1.1.2 Alternate Flow 2
    The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when ICSE returns an error.
  7. Service consumer invokes service SV012 on ESB using ModifyVisaApplicationRequest.
  8. SV012 creates an ICSE request message according to the rules described in chapter 2.1 (ICSE Service Provider).
    a. For each single Attribute a PermissionRequestInfo-Element is created.
    b. For each Child Object at least one Event-Element is created.
    c. For each Note one Event-Element is created.
  9. Service SV012 invokes ICSE sending the request message.
  10. ICSE receives the request and encounters an error.
  11. SV012 detects the error and transforms ICSE Error into Enterprise Error
  12. SV012 passes a response with this Enterprise Error to the consumer.
    1.1.2 ModifyApplicant
    1.1.2.1 Service Flow for ModifyApplicant
    The service receives the request message from the consumer. The Message contains the either a request to modify the association to the primary Visa Applicant or to modify the role of a Visa Applicant or to modify both the association to the primary Visa Applicant and the role of a Visa Applicant and/or to add a new Applicant to a Visa Application.

Then the Flow sends an accordingly populated ApplicationMaintenanceRequest message to ICSE. Dependent on which element of the choice group is passed by the consumer different elements of the ApplicationMaintenanceRequest are populated:
o In case of ModifyApplicantAssociationAndOrRoleType the UpdateClntRole Element with both children (oldclnt and updtclnt) is populated.
o In case of AddNewApplicant the AddClntRole Element is populated.

ICSE will then execute this request and return an acknowledgement message back to service SV012 where a response message is returned to the consumer.

The detail of this flow is as follows:

  1. Service consumer invokes service SV012 on ESB using ModifyVisaApplicationRequest.
  2. SV012 creates a ICSE request message
  3. SV012 invokes ICSE sending the request message.
  4. ICSE receives the request and tries processes the updates for the specified visa application or the specified Visa Applicant(s).
  5. ICSE then sends an acknowledgement message back to service SV012.
  6. Service SV012 sends a successful response message to the consumer.
    1.1.2.2 Alternate Flow 1
    The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when CDH returns an error.
  7. Service consumer invokes service SV012 on ESB using ModifyVisaApplicationRequest.
  8. SV012 receives the Enterprise Error and passes a response with this Enterprise Error to the consumer
    1.1.2.3 Alternate Flow 2
    The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when ICSE returns an error.
  9. Service consumer invokes service SV012 on ESB using ModifyVisaApplicationRequest.
  10. SV012 creates a ICSE request message
  11. SV012 invokes ICSE sending the request message.
  12. ICSE receives the request and encounters an error.
  13. SV012 detects the error and transforms ICSE Error into Enterprise Error
  14. SV012 passes a response with this Enterprise Error to the consumer.

Transformation

To see the latest message mappings refer to the Micro Design document DIMA_DCD d15 Service Specification - SV012 - v03.0 Modify Visa Application.xls
Specific mappings required:
1) Retrieving ICSE Reversal event type codes from ICSE event type codes. ESB code mapping table to be used for this.
2) Retrieving ICSE Qualifier code from ICSE event type code and Portal reason type codes. ESB code mapping table to be used for this.
3) Mapping required for transforming EmploymentVerificationStatus, EmploymentVerifiedFlag under Employment History, to one ICSE field which then gets stored. The combination of the two fields determines which value to be sent to ICSE.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
